It‚Äôs equal to half the area of the rectangle actually
The top triangles have common height... when you add the areas up  you actually get 1/2 x common height x total base length
Bottom triangles have common height 2. Adding them up  1/2 x common height 2 x total base length
Common height 1 + common height 2 = width of rectangle
If u split the rectangles into different parts where each triangle is half of the part it is in  u will see that it is half f the entire rectangle
